[[File:Neumes, Manuscript, XIIth century.jpg|thumb|right|Armenian [[music manuscript]] with khaz [[neume]]s, 12th century ([[Matenadaran]])]] '''Khaz''' ({{lang-hy|խազ}}) is an [[Armenians|Armenian]] [[neume]], one of a set of special signs (plural: khaz or '''khazes''') constituting the traditional system of [[musical notation]] that has been used to transcribe [[Music of Armenia#Religious music|religious Armenian music]] since the 8th century.<ref>[[Vahan Kurkjian]] (1958) ''A History of Armenia'', chapter XLV: [http://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/E/Gazetteer/Places/Asia/Armenia/_Texts/KURARM/45*.html "Armenian Music Secular and Religious"]</ref><ref>''Armenian Neume System of Notation: Study and Analysis'' (2013) chapter 2: "Ancient Armenian manuscripts and their significance for the study of musical khaz notation" [https://books.google.com/books?id=csQeAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA43 google books preview]</ref>
